    "In particular, the generalist biocatalyst variant MLYPPT features unusually high degrees of loop flexibility, better accommodating both the borane and silane substrates.",
    "This finding has broad implications beyond the development of effective borylation and silylation biocatalysts.",
    "Our work demonstrated the effectiveness of leveraging protein evolutionary data using ML for cold-start enzyme library design in newto-nature biocatalysis.",
    "Without relying on the mechanistic considerations of newly designed enzymatic processes, the evolutionary information reveals the sequence patterns deemed by nature as prerequisites for function, such as those related to structural stability or biophysical properties.",
    "By harnessing evolutionary information, MODIFY excludes detrimental mutations and designs effective biocatalyst libraries for the development of synthetically useful enzyme functions."
